text: Starved Rock State Park is a state park in the U.S. state of Illinois. It is made by the many canyons within its . It is located just southeast of the village of Utica in LaSalle County, Illinois, along the south bank of the Illinois River. The park hosts over two million visitors annually, the most for any Illinois state park.Fun Facts about Illinois Tourism , Illinois Issues, University of Illinois at Springfield, June 2011 ==References== Category:State parks in the United States Category:Geography of Illinois
